  <entry>
    <title>Recent Reading: Meljean Brook</title>
    <id>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/</id>
    <updated>2012-06-13T23:34:33-05:00</updated>
    <published>2012-06-13T23:34:33-05:00</published>
    <author>
      <name>T. Kurt Bond</name>
    </author>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/"/>
    <summary type="html">&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;From the series &lt;cite class="series"&gt;The Iron Seas&lt;/cite&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;The Iron Duke&lt;/cite&gt;, by Meljean Brook; copyright 2010 by Melissa Kahn;
ISBN 978-0-425-23667-3.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;cite&gt;Heart of Steel&lt;/cite&gt;, by Meljean Brook; copyright 2011 by Melissa
Kahn; ISB 978-0-425-24330-5.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;From the front cover: «“Meljean Brook has brilliantly defined he
new genre of steampunk romance.” — Jayne Ann Krentz, &lt;cite&gt;New York
Times&lt;/cite&gt; bestselling author».&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These are very good.  The back covers list them as “paranormal
romance” &lt;a class="footnote-reference brackets" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/#pr-section" id="footnote-reference-1" role="doc-noteref"&gt;&lt;span class="fn-bracket"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;1&lt;span class="fn-bracket"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, but I suspect that they form exemplars for
a new genre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Her setting is interestingly and greatly altered history.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Stories by Meljean Brook appear in (at least) the following
anthologies: &lt;cite&gt;Hot Spell&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Wild Thing&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;First Blood&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Must
Love Hellhounds&lt;/cite&gt;, &lt;cite&gt;Burning Up&lt;/cite&gt;, and &lt;cite&gt;Angels of Darkness&lt;/cite&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;!-- Explicit sex: clit, cock --&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;aside class="footnote brackets" id="pr-section" role="note"&gt;
&lt;span class="label"&gt;&lt;span class="fn-bracket"&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a role="doc-backlink" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2012/06/13/meljean-brook/#footnote-reference-1"&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="fn-bracket"&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The local library I frequent most often has a
separate section for paranormal romance now, though these were
shelved in general fiction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/aside&gt;</summary>
